<TEXT>
a new centerleft government headed by 
former prime minister steingrimur hermannsson took office 
wednesday enacting an immediate pricewage freeze and devaluating 
the icelandic krona 
the government in a statement issued immediately after assuming 
power announced a 3 percent devaluation of the krona a wage 
freeze until midfebruary and a price freeze until the end of 
february in a bid to stave off icelands acute economic problems 
thorsteinn palssons 15month centerright coalition government 
resigned last week after failing to agree on economic policy 
hermannssons ninemember cabinet groups his centrist 
progressive party the social democratic party and the leftist 
peoples alliance it was sworn in by president vigdis 
finnbogadottir following negotiations among the political parties 
without an election being called 
hermannsson said his governments top goal was to bring down the 
annual rate of inflation from its present level of 25 percent to 
around five percent by the middle of next year 
the fishing industry accounting for twothirds of this north 
atlantic island nations foreign exchange earnings has been 
especially hardhit by the crisis and is reported near bankruptcy 
the fishing industry has demanded a sharp devaluation of the 
krona to cut the price of its exports making them more 
competitive but a currency devaluation automatically pushes up the 
price of imports from abroad 
one us dollar was worth 4676 kronur immediately before 
wednesdays devaluation the third this year 
hermannsson was foreign minister in palssons government which 
took office in june 1987 
under a nato agreement this nation of 250000 people is the 
site of a major us air base at keflavik 25 miles southwest of 
the capital reykjavik guarding strategic sea routes 
</TEXT>
