<TEXT>
portauprince haiti ap a demonstration set for thursday in 
support of the soldiers who overthrew the regime of lt gen henri 
namphy was canceled after soldiers seized an arms cache and 
arrested two men radio stations said 
radio haiti inter said troops on wednesday arrested two men 
identified as clifford mayard paul and jean marie gouffe at the ido 
lele a luxury hotel on the heights of petionville overlooking 
portauprince the capital 
in the mens hotel room the soldiers found three uzi machine 
guns grenades and grenade launchers the radio said 
opposition leader louie dejoie jr head of the national 
industrial and agricultural party and a member of the committee for 
democratic understanding told the associated press late wednesday 
it seems that the government is doing its job which is to disarm 
the macoutes 
it was a reference to the dread tonton macoutes the private 
militia during the 29year duvalier dynasty that suppressed all 
opposition 
the arrests were made in line with a communique issued tuesday 
night by the minister of defense and interior col carl 
dorfainvil calling on the people to hand in any unregistered 
weapon to the nearest military authority 
wednesdays developments prompted leaders of the confederation 
of democratic unity to urge the people not to demonstrate 
the confederation was the largest and most influential of the 
six organizations that called for the demonstration hailing 
namphys ouster nearly two weeks ago 
in a communique read over radio haiti inter the confederation 
said the macoutes are getting ready to take reprisals against 
the demonstrators 
confederation leaders told the ap the decision to cancel the 
demonstration also was influenced by reports over radio soleil of 
many calls from listeners saying that those who had perpetrated 
the massacre at the aborted nov 29 elections last year were 
going to wreak havoc on the demonstration 
thugs and soldiers killed 34 people on on nov 29 1987 the day 
general elections were being held forcing the elections to be 
called off 
the other five organizations that called the demonstration did 
not react to immediately to the confederations announcement 
dejoie whose organization is not one of the five agreed with the 
call for cancellation 
the planned demonstration had not had the support of syvio 
claude leader of the haitian christian democratic party and one of 
the most influential politicians in the democratic opposition 
claude said over radio metropole wednesday afternoon that a 
demonstration in favor of the government is a little premature 
claude said that lt gen prosper avril the new president has 
just come to power he is not in the camp of the people but in the 
duvalierist camp we ought to wait a while to see whether avril 
is on the same wavelength as the soldiers 
soldiers have repeatedly said they want to purge the army and 
government of duvalierists 
the demonstration was announced on wednesday by the leftleaning 
confederation of democratic unity the autonomous union of haitian 
workers and four other civic action groups 
hundreds of striking government workers of the state flour mill 
meanwhile demonstrated in the capital wednesday protesting the 
appointment of yves jose a duvalierist civil servant to head 
their enterprise 
the appointment of jose former general director and state 
secretary of the finance ministry under ousted president 
jeanclaude duvalier was announced over state television tuesday 
night 
a workers delegation briefly met with avril in the national 
palace to discuss the contested appointment in an interview with 
radio haitiinter ady jean maxime vicepresident of the company 
union said the delegation then reached a compromise solution with 
finance minister leonce thelusma 
strikes began wednesday in the port authority and national 
credit bank after management leadership 
on sept 17 avril was named president of the military 
government by the rankandfile soldiers of the presidential guard 
who had just ousted namphy namphy had deposed the civilian 
president leslie manigat three months before 
avril and the leader of the soldiers sgt joseph heubreux are 
governing in tandem 
duvalier who succeeded his late father francois papa doc 
duvalier fled into exile in france during a popular uprising in 
february 1986 
