<TEXT>
fewer flowers and no officiallysanctioned 
fireworks will grace chinas national day on oct 1 this year 
the beijing government currently trying to rein in public 
sector overspending that is emptying the treasury and fueling 
inflation has announced that frugality must rule in celebrating 
the 39th anniversary of the founding of the peoples republic of 
china 
the official china daily today quoted beijing officials as 
saying there will be 340000 fewer potted plants in the flower 
display traditionally set up in central tiananmen square for the 
national holiday 
no official fireworks will be set off although lasers will be 
used to create an atmosphere the daily said 
government and party leaders will gather at the great hall of 
the people friday evening for a reception but no other organized 
parties and entertainment programs in the hall will be allowed 
the report said shanghai and fujian province have banned all 
festival dinner parties using public funds and the government has 
ordered state units against reckless distribution of 
unauthorized bonuses subsidies allowances and food 
the daily said there will be more meat poultry and eggs 
available this year for residents in beijing shanghai and other 
large cities to celebrate at home 
the beijing government recently has imposed taxes on official 
banquets banned giftgiving by officials and ordered cutbacks in 
purchases of cars and other consumer items as part of a campaign to 
combat outofcontrol spending by public offices 
chinese workers receive three days off for national day and the 
streets are lined with chrysanthemums and other flowers this year 
many are arranged to depict dragons to mark the year of the dragon 
in tiananmen square besides the flower displays workers are 
erecting portraits of marx engels lenin and stalin which go up 
every national day and may day 
