the dangers from the chemicals were revealed to residents 
eventually 728 homes in a 50block area were evacuated the 
elementary school and 228 houses were demolished 
the state and federal governments filed multimilliondollar 
lawsuits against hookers parent company occidental petroleum 
corp much of that litigation is pending 
the dump site has been fenced off and surrounded with clay and 
plastic liners to prevent the chemicals from leaking into the air 
or ground water corroding drums of dioxins and other chemicals 
have been separated and complex runoff and monitoring systems built 
