the lawsuit which was filed in january 1981 and went to trial 
last october alleges that the 1967 consolidation of county schools 
fostered racial segregation 
the consolidation created a countywide school board to oversee 
the operations of eight existing local school districts but the 
consolidation left faculty and student assignments in control of 
the local district boards 
fiftyfive percent of the countys 43512 students are black 
