the columbus ind republic on air pollution 
those hazy days of summer are behind us too bad the same cant 
be said for air pollution 
according to a report acid rain has landed in our own 
backyard no longer can we smugly dismiss it as someone elses 
problem 
acid rain occurs when sulfur dioxide emitted by the tall stacks 
of power plants and factories mixes with moisture in the 
atmosphere the six states bordering the ohio river account for 
almost 40 percent of this countrys sulfur dioxide pollution 
but prevailing winds were thought to carry the pollutants north 
to canada and east toward new england 
industry particularly midwestern power companies has long 
maintained that the costs of additional antipollution 
equipment will drive up consumer costs while making it less 
competitive 
those arguments sounded convincing enough when midwesterners 
thought they had little to worry about now theres another price 
to pay 
