the main opposition group accused the 
military government wednesday of killing nearly 1000 people since 
a sept 18 coup and it registered as a political party to 
challenge 26 years of authoritarian rule 
a second prodemocracy group made up of followers of former 
prime minister u nu also registered wednesday and a third 
opposition political party announced its formation 
some burmese said soldiers were sealing off urban centers to 
prevent people from fleeing to rebelcontrolled areas to carry on 
the fight for democracy 
several hundred students have fled to the thaiburmese border 
where large areas are controlled by the karen mon shan and other 
minority groups the students are seeking military training from 
the karens perhaps the most powerful of the rebel groups 
