those who dont abide by the partys discipline must be 
punished the party warned in its harshest indictment of the role 
that officials and party members have played in the growing 
economic disorder 
the editorial probably was approved by the partys top 
policymaking central committee which began a closeddoor 
fiveday session monday the committee is expected to approve a 
twoyear moratorium on price reform and measures to control 
inflation and excessive capital construction 
chinas supreme court meanwhile ordered lower courts to punish 
government officials found guilty of profiteering and speculation 
those officials have seriously disrupted the normal economic 
environment and hampered the smooth progress of chinas reform and 
construction the court said 
it ordered an end to fining guilty officials rather than 
bringing criminal charges against them 
inflation has soared from about 7 percent last year to more than 
20 percent this year overspending by government offices and 
staterun factories and widespread speculation have been major 
factors although issuing too much currency and loose credit also 
is to blame 
