said the study tells you specifically what things will make it 
better for adults and therefore for children 
more than half of the school staff members surveyed reported 
problems with inadequate working space which they attributed to 
overenrollment reductions in class sizes and space requirements 
for special programs 
the study said one respondent underscored the pessimism by 
noting that her school had turned closets into classrooms placed 
