a mexican drug trafficker was found guilty 
wednesday of aiding and abetting the 1985 torture murder of a us 
drug agent and his pilot he was the third man convicted in the 
case which strained usmexican relations 
jesus felix gutierrez 38 was found guilty by a federal jury of 
helping mexican drug baron rafael caro quintero escape to costa 
rica after the brutal 1985 murder of drug enforcement 
administration agent enrique camarena and his pilot alfredo zavala 
avelar 
felixs attorney had contended there was insufficent evidence to 
convict the former los angeles seafood store owner and suggested 
the government altered evidence 
the key evidence against felix was the testimony of a government 
informant who said he heard the defendant discuss his role in 
arranging caros escape prosecutors also showed jurors entries on 
felixs passport indicating he had preceded caro to costa rica and 
left after caro arrived 
earlier jurors convicted renee verdugo uruidez 36 and raul 
lopez alvarez 28 of conspiring and participating in the 
kidnapmurders of camarena and zavala 
verdugo who was said to be caros chief lieutenant in a 
multimilliondollar marijuana smuggling ring and lopez a former 
member of the mexican state police face possible life imprisonment 
lopez is to be sentenced oct 24 and verdugos sentencing is 
set for oct 26 
felix who is serving time on a cocaine trafficking conviction 
faces a possible maximum of 10 years in prison 
the battered bodies of camarena and his pilot were found buried 
at a remote ranch outside guadalajara on march 5 1985 camarena 
had been kidnapped outside the us consulate in guadalajara on 
feb 7 1985 
evidence showed the agent and pilot were tortured with redhot 
metal pipes and beaten so severely that camarenas skull was 
crushed 
prosecutors theorized the killings were retribution for dea 
raids on caros marijuana plantations 
attorneys for the three defendants said they were scapegoats 
used by the mexican and american governments to close an 
embarrassing internationally sensitive case 
nine men were indicted in los angeles but only three were tried 
here one defendant died four including caro were tried in 
mexico on narcotics and murder charges 
