<TEXT>
pope john paul ii is so welltraveled that 
the focus has shifted to where he hasnt visited instead of where 
he has already stopped 
since setting out for the dominican republic and mexico three 
months after assuming the papacy 10 years ago john paul has made 
39 foreign pilgrimages stopping in 72 countries 
easily the most traveled pope in history he has flown some 
370000 miles including his trip to southern africa in 
midseptember thats like traveling from the earth to the moon and 
more than halfway back 
but if he has visited every continent except antartica he has 
yet to visit a number of key spots for varying reasons they 
include the soviet union china cuba and the holy land 
on the september trip john paul was to skirt south africa on 
the fivecountry pilgrimage but found himself stopping briefly in 
the segregated country when bad weather closed in the airport in 
lesotho the pope said the time wasnt ripe to visit south africa 
but that he wanted to make a regular visit there someday 
early in his pontificate john paul described himself as a 
pilgrim messenger who would travel the world to see his flock he 
has kept his word far surpassing pope paul vi the first jet age 
pontiff who became known as the apostle on the move 
paul made nine overseas trips between 1964 and 1970 when weary 
and 72 he halted all foreign travel 
john paul has made nine trips to latin america alone reflecting 
the importance the vatican attaches to a region expected to contain 
half the worlds roman catholics by the turn of the century 
he has also paid four visits to africa where the church has 
been making inroads as well as three pilgrimages to his native 
poland and two to the united states 
the trips are central to john pauls papacy he has bristled at 
suggestions he should spend more time at the vatican vatican 
statistics say he is away less than 8 percent of his pontificate 
or that the trips cost too much 
he chose a bishops conference in mexico on his first trip to 
reject marxistinspired liberation theology he influenced the mood 
of his fellow poles during his 1979 pilgrimage that helped lead to 
the birth of the solidarity free trade union and he expounded 
church teaching to americans in 1987 saying that dissent was 
incompatible with being a good catholic 
still to come are a trip later this year to strasbourg france 
to address the european parliament and a visit to scandinavia next 
year 
john pauls hopes of visiting the soviet union have not yet been 
realized he has disclosed that hes been prevented from visiting 
lithuania the roman catholic stronghold in the soviet union and 
insists that he must be allowed to visit with his flock on any 
pilgrimage 
the holy land is an especially delicate case paul vi made a 
whirlwind visit to israel and jordan in 1964 but that was three 
years before israel took over predominantly arab east jerusalem and 
the west bank in the 1967 war 
the vatican has not established diplomatic relations with israel 
and john paul has stressed that the palestinians like the jews 
have a right to a homeland 
the vatican says it is premature for the pope to visit apartheid 
south africa and communist cuba there has been no invitation from 
china which broke relations with the vatican in 1957 and 
established its own breakaway catholic church 
