his quarter century in city government 
without a doubt i think the stock market affects the market 
for new construction and for investors who might have been here 
earlier sweney said his city 30 miles north of denver expects 
to attract 1000 new jobs this year but believes those jobs might 
have been filled and working sooner if not for the market 
the mayor a retired city administrator also took a personal 
hit from the crash it affected the pension fund that im drawing 
from he said 
