street said samuel ehrenhalt regional commissioner in new york 
of the us bureau of labor statistics i dont think weve seen 
the end of the process 
mari terzaghi a clinical psychologist who specializes in 
patients from the financial community says she still treats many 
people suffering from what she calls the identity crash 
triggered by black monday when people develop a sense of 
themselves in money symbols then lose them because of investments 
or jobs they feel a sense of annihilation she explains 
the situation really has not gotten better ms terzaghi 
said noting that wall street types continue to come to her because 
